0 0 1-2-2v-10a2 2 0 0 1 2-2H8a.5.5 0 0 1 .35.14c.1.1.15.22.15.35a.5.5 0 0 1-.15.35.5.5 0 0 1-.35.15H6.4c-.5 0-.9.4-.9.9v10.2a.9.9 0 0 0 .9.9h11.2c.5 0 .9-.4.9-.9V8.96c0-.5-.4-.9-.9-.9H16a.5.5 0 0 1 0-1z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg><div class="j i d"><p class="be b bf z dt">Share</p></div></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><figure class="na nb nc nd ne nf mx my paragraph-image"><div role="button" tabindex="0" class="ng nh fg ni bg nj"><div class="mx my mz"><picture><source srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*Q5m86ifQLPmFjIqI9_TH7w.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*Q5m86ifQLPmFjIqI9_TH7w.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*Q5m86ifQLPmFjIqI9_TH7w.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*Q5m86ifQLPmFjIqI9_TH7w.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*Q5m86ifQLPmFjIqI9_TH7w.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*Q5m86ifQLPmFjIqI9_TH7w.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*Q5m86ifQLPmFjIqI9_TH7w.png 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*Q5m86ifQLPmFjIqI9_TH7w.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*Q5m86ifQLPmFjIqI9_TH7w.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*Q5m86ifQLPmFjIqI9_TH7w.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*Q5m86ifQLPmFjIqI9_TH7w.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*Q5m86ifQLPmFjIqI9_TH7w.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*Q5m86ifQLPmFjIqI9_TH7w.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*Q5m86ifQLPmFjIqI9_TH7w.png 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"/><img alt="" class="bg me nk c" width="700" height="363" loading="eager" role="presentation"/></picture></div></div></figure><p id="6315" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj">Italy — A <a class="oj iv fb" href="https://medium.com/u/5ed69ff9cfb0?source=post_page-----24f2161bb59a--------------------------------" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Star Atlas</a> player belonging to the guild <a class="af ok" href="https://staratlasitalia.com/" rel="noopener ugc nofollow" target="_blank">Star Atlas Italia</a> is the winner of a $30,000 star ship, the Pearce D9, during the latest series of Star Atlas Surge Events. The Hologram News Network reached out to the winner, <a class="af ok" href="https://twitter.com/Xx9DeadshoT4xX" rel="noopener ugc nofollow" target="_blank">Deadshot</a>, to find out how he feels about winning such a coveted prize.</p><p id="3cac" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj">Star Atlas recently hosted a Star Atlas Escape Velocity Surge Event, where the odds of finding a particular tier reward is significantly increased. For this event in particular, the odds of a Platinum reward were increased by 150%. Below is our interview with Deadshot.</p><figure class="om on oo op oq nf mx my paragraph-image"><div role="button" tabindex="0" class="ng nh fg ni bg nj"><div class="mx my ol"><picture><source srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/0*ecEv5EkpXqfMNc8h 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/0*ecEv5EkpXqfMNc8h 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/0*ecEv5EkpXqfMNc8h 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/0*ecEv5EkpXqfMNc8h 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/0*ecEv5EkpXqfMNc8h 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/0*ecEv5EkpXqfMNc8h 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*ecEv5EkpXqfMNc8h 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*ecEv5EkpXqfMNc8h 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*ecEv5EkpXqfMNc8h 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*ecEv5EkpXqfMNc8h 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*ecEv5EkpXqfMNc8h 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*ecEv5EkpXqfMNc8h 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*ecEv5EkpXqfMNc8h 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*ecEv5EkpXqfMNc8h 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"/><img alt="" class="bg me nk c" width="700" height="394" loading="lazy" role="presentation"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class="or fc os mx my ot ou be b bf z dt">Star Atlas Escape Velocity Surge Event 150x Platinum Tier</figcaption></figure><p id="a539" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj"><em class="ov">Note: Due to language barriers, this interview was conducted over text with the assistance of Google Translate.</em></p><h1 id="23c6" class="ow ox gr be oy oz pa pb pc pd pe pf pg ph pi pj pk pl pm pn po pp pq pr ps pt bj">Deadshot (Star Atlas Italia) — Winner of the Perace D9 in Star Atlas Escape Velocity Surge</h1><p id="1067" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no pu nq nr ns pv nu nv nw pw ny nz oa px oc od oe py og oh oi gk bj"><strong class="nn gs">Krigs: </strong>Congratulations on winning such a marvelous prize! How did you feel in the moment when you realized you won a capital ship?</p><p id="4c73" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj"><strong class="nn gs">Deadshot: </strong>The moment I found the capital ship, I was filled with joy and amazement. It was a crucial moment and I could not believe my eyes. Knowing that I was live streaming with the rest of my guild mates made it all the more special.</p><p id="ffde" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj"><strong class="nn gs">Krigs: </strong>How long have you been playing Escape Velocity and do you play everyday. How long do you play each time?</p><p id="f07d" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj"><strong class="nn gs">Deadshot: </strong>I’ve been playing Escape Velocity since day one with my guild friends. I play almost every day, dedicating an average of at least 1 hour maybe even more to each game session.</p><p id="2b77" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj"><strong class="nn gs">Krigs: </strong>During the Surge event, were you trying any particular strategy?</p><p id="44ad" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj"><strong class="nn gs">Deadshot: </strong>There is no precise strategy, I have 16 ships lined up and I move them up and down, but during the event a particular thing happened while joking with a friend of mine, who was on my lines. I told him you can move, then I’ll move, and moved and 10 lines later the D9 came.</p><figure class="om on oo op oq nf mx my paragraph-image"><div role="button" tabindex="0" class="ng nh fg ni bg nj"><div class="mx my pz"><picture><source srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*RStFf_pd8PYA64WmSqpCow.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*RStFf_pd8PYA64WmSqpCow.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*RStFf_pd8PYA64WmSqpCow.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*RStFf_pd8PYA64WmSqpCow.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*RStFf_pd8PYA64WmSqpCow.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*RStFf_pd8PYA64WmSqpCow.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*RStFf_pd8PYA64WmSqpCow.png 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*RStFf_pd8PYA64WmSqpCow.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*RStFf_pd8PYA64WmSqpCow.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*RStFf_pd8PYA64WmSqpCow.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*RStFf_pd8PYA64WmSqpCow.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*RStFf_pd8PYA64WmSqpCow.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*RStFf_pd8PYA64WmSqpCow.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*RStFf_pd8PYA64WmSqpCow.png 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"/><img alt="" class="bg me nk c" width="700" height="368" loading="lazy" role="presentation"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class="or fc os mx my ot ou be b bf z dt">Pearce D9 Salvage Ship</figcaption></figure><p id="f2db" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj"><strong class="nn gs">Krigs:</strong> This is quite a prestigious event for the guild. How long have you been apart of Star Atlas Italia?</p><p id="8a9f" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj"><strong class="nn gs">Deadshot: </strong>I have been part of Star Atlas Italia (SAI) for over a year and a half. I have found many friends and playmates. Being a player we find ourselves in tournaments with other guilds such as The Club, Bulk, Rome and slowly I have also grown in my guild. Currently I am a squad leader and directed in the last event the organization of 650 ships belonging to guild players. I aspire to become a fleet commander of SAI.</p><p id="1072" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj"><strong class="nn gs">Krigs: </strong>The D9 is quite a unique ship in that there currently aren’t many available. Do you have any plans for the D9?</p><p id="6fb1" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj"><strong class="nn gs">Deadshot: </strong>Currently I do not because it was unexpected, but surely together with my guild and friends we will make the most of it</p><p id="e0c6" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj"><strong class="nn gs">Krigs: </strong>Did you share the news with anyone that doesn’t play Star Atlas? Family, relatives, friends? How did they react?</p><p id="620a" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj"><strong class="nn gs">Deadshot: </strong>Yes, I shared it with my family and they were amazed and did not believe it. I also showed them the ship which they liked very much. some of my friends convinced them to come and see it as it will be given to me. I will spawn it in the guild server SAI to make the next rally with all ships.</p><p id="b507" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj"><strong class="nn gs">Krigs</strong>: Is there anything else about yourself you want to tell the community?</p><p id="0b0b" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj"><strong class="nn gs">Deadshot</strong>: Yes, the first night I found it I couldn&#x27;t sleep! The next day I turned on the PC and thought I&#x27;m going to check because I still didn&#x27;t believe it that it was out. I invite the community to never stop trying because yes sometimes something beautiful comes and I hope it&#x27;s just the beginning for all of us! Viva Star Atlas! You are amazing keep it up and you will always have the support of the community</p></div></div></div><div class="ab ca qa qb qc qd" role="separator"><span class="qe bx bl qf qg qh"></span><span class="qe bx bl qf qg qh"></span><span class="qe bx bl qf qg"></span></div><div class="gk gl gm gn go"><div class="ab ca"><div class="ch bg fw fx fy fz"><h1 id="335b" class="ow ox gr be oy oz qi pb pc pd qj pf pg ph qk pj pk pl ql pn po pp qm pr ps pt bj">About the Author</h1><p id="223e" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no pu nq nr ns pv nu nv nw pw ny nz oa px oc od oe py og oh oi gk bj"><a class="af ok" href="https://medium.com/u/41e0c5b141f1" rel="noopener">Krigs</a> is a pioneer in the world of Star Atlas, having founded The Hologram News Network — an independent meta-news organization that keeps players up to date on all developments regarding Star Atlas. An ardent supporter of emerging technologies, Krigs has been covering this game for over a year and believes passionately in their power to revolutionize our collective gaming experience.</p><p id="82bc" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj">Follow on Social Media:</p><p id="7089" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj"><a class="af ok" href="https://open.spotify.com/show/2mxndrDW6yPfpS350ijzjt?si=ec7c717f998240d6" rel="noopener ugc nofollow" target="_blank">Podcast</a> | <a class="af ok" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCDa-YxgNG6A9xpH1qyP0OaQ" rel="noopener ugc nofollow" target="_blank">YouTube</a> | <a class="af ok" href="https://twitter.com/home" rel="noopener ugc nofollow" target="_blank">Twitter</a> | <a class="af ok" href="https://twitter.com/home" rel="noopener ugc nofollow" target="_blank">Instagram</a> | <a class="af ok" href="https://thehologram.io/" rel="noopener ugc nofollow" target="_blank">Web</a></p><h1 id="57e0" class="ow ox gr be oy oz pa pb pc pd pe pf pg ph pi pj pk pl pm pn po pp pq pr ps pt bj">About The Hologram</h1><p id="4cf3" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no pu nq nr ns pv nu nv nw pw ny nz oa px oc od oe py og oh oi gk bj"><a class="af ok" href="https://medium.com/the-hologram" rel="noopener">The Hologram</a> is Star Atlas’ first and only independent news network. Our vision is to become the most trusted source of information about Star Atlas and a voice for the whole community. Readers can expect a high standard from our reporting and staff. Our promise to you: we will not publish anything that hasn’t been thoroughly researched and based on the best facts available.</p><p id="c062" class="pw-post-body-paragraph nl nm gr nn b no np nq nr ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi gk bj">The Hologram is not endorsed by the <a class="af ok" href="https://staratlas.com/" rel="noopener ugc nofollow" target="_blank">Star Atlas</a> team. Any information published by The Hologram or its writers should be considered as informational in nature and does not constitute any financial advice.</p></div></div></div></div></section></div></div></article><div class="ab ca"><div class="ch bg fw fx fy fz"></div></div></div><div class="ab ca"><div class="ch bg fw fx fy fz"><div class="qn qo ab jc"><div class="qp ab"><a class="qq ax am ao" rel="noopener follow" href="/tag/star-atlas?source=post_page-----24f2161bb59a---------------star_atlas-----------------"><div class="qr fg cw qs gb qt qu be b bf z bj qv">Star Atlas</div></a></d